# Core Project Rules

- Output ASCII only. No emojis in markdown, commits, or terminal.
- Type-hint all Python function signatures.
- Catch specific exceptions; no bare `except:`.
- Data outputs go to `data/`. Visual outputs go to `assets/`.
- Read `ops/CURRENT.md` before starting work. Open only the files needed for the active task.
- Prefer `.head()`, `.shape`, or schema summaries over reading full data files into context.
- Do not modify `AGENTS.md` unless explicitly instructed.
